disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Loaded Dice.

blurb.value: Upon killing a unit, Twisted Fate rolls his 'lucky' dice receiving anywhere between 1 and 6 bonus gold.

description.value: Innate: Every time Twisted Fate kills an enemy, he gains 1 − 6 (based on probability).

description2.value: Since his dice is loaded, Twisted Fate has an increased chance of gaining 6.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * The expected bonus gold gained per unit killed is 4.
notes.description: Displays additional information with effect table to the right.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Pick a Card.

blurb.value: Twisted Fate chooses a magic card from his deck, and uses that for his next attack, causing bonus effects.

description.value: Active: Twisted Fate cycles through three cards for 6 seconds, hovering each for 0.5 seconds at a time. Choosing one by reactivating Pick a Card converts Twisted Fate's next basic attack within 6 seconds to have a 0.25-second cast time, deal magic damage, and apply an additional effect based on the card selected. The attack applies both on-hit and spell effects, but cannot critically strike.

description2.value: Recast - Blue Card: Restores  mana.

description3.value: Recast - Red Card: Deals magic damage around the target and slows all enemies hit for 2.5 seconds.

description4.value: Recast - Gold Card: Stuns the target.

description5.value: Pick a Card's recast can be used while affected by crowd control.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: *The initial cast counts as an ability activation for the purposes of on-cast effects such as Spellblade, charging Spellbinder, and stacking Force Pulse. Recasting the ability does not. The enhanced attack triggers against turrets but not jungle plants and wards. It will not trigger against any other structures. Pick a Card triggers on-hit effects and thus will stack and trigger Stacked Deck. The first card shown is random but the order always remains the same ( Blue Card, Red Card, Gold Card, repeat). Upon activation, an indicator visible to allies and enemies appears above Twisted Fate to show him shuffling his deck of cards while remaining in the same order, the card he can choose at every moment glows over the others. The selected card is specified for the duration of the enhanced attack. PENDING FOR TEST The interval until the next card is hovered is 0.528 seconds every time, instead of some times 0.528 and other times 0.495.
notes.description: Displays additional information with effect table to the right.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Stacked Deck.

blurb.value: Every 4 attacks, Twisted Fate deals bonus damage. In addition, his Attack Speed is increased.

description.value: Passive: Twisted Fate gains  bonus attack speed.

description2.value: Twisted Fate gains a stack of Stacked Deck on-hit, up to a maximum of three.

description3.value: At 3 stacks, his next basic attack against non-structures consumes the stacks on-hit to deal bonus magic damage.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Destiny.

blurb.value: Twisted Fate predicts the fortunes of his foes, revealing all enemy champions and enabling the use of Gate, which teleports Twisted Fate to any target location in 1.5 seconds.

description.value: Active: Twisted Fate summons an identifying eyeball above all targetable enemy champions for a few seconds, revealing them for the duration. Destiny can be recast after 0.5 seconds.

description2.value: Recast: Twisted Fate channels for 1.5 seconds and then blinks to the target location upon completion, destroying all projectiles targeting him in the process.

notes.value: *The second cast's name is Gate. Both casts count as ability activations for the purposes of on-cast effects such as Spellblade, charging Spellbinder, and stacking Force Pulse. Destiny will reveal wards and stealthed traps if they are within sight range of a revealed enemy champion. The nearsight from Paranoia will overpower the reveal from Destiny regardless of which one was cast first (enemy champions can still be revealed by Destiny after Paranoia ends if durations permit). Using the recast will inform allies with a ping. Both allies and enemies can see an indicator at the targeted location of where Twisted Fate will appear.
